HEADWORD: Inquinate
<hw>In"qui*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inquinatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>inquinare</ets> to defile.]</ety>
<def>To defile; to pollute; to contaminate; to befoul.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

